The diagram includes two lines: one representing the data line stable (DSL) component, and another representing the change of data allowed (CDA) component. The DSL circuit has three input pins and two output pins, with the input pins connected to the DSL component and the output pins connected to the CDA component.

The diagram also includes a legend that explains the different components in the circuit, such as the data line stable (DSL), change of data allowed (CDA), and dark void (DV). The legend is located at the bottom right corner of the image.
